  (B) A summary of how the Patent Non-Assertion Covenant applies to the
      NQP Patents. The Covenant itself is the controlling patent
      instrument.

Commercial relationships — Foundation conformance certification and the
Enqpy™ marks, high-performance proprietary implementations, support,
integration, advisory, and indemnity — are described in Section C and at
https://enqpy.com/use.html. None of those relationships is required in
order to use, implement, or deploy the Enqpy™ cipher itself; the Covenant
makes the cipher patent-safe for all conforming use.

