----------------------------------------------------------------

Permission is hereby granted to any person obtaining a copy of the
Enqpy™ reference implementation in this repository, free of charge,
to:

  - Clone the repository, build, and execute the implementation
  - Run the embedded self-test and benchmark harnesses
  - Analyze the source code for evaluation, review, and academic
    purposes
  - Compare implementation output against the paper and FCD test
    vectors
  - Cite the implementation in academic and professional work with
    appropriate attribution

Permission is not granted under this section to:

  - Redistribute NQP's reference source code in this repository,
    whether modified or unmodified, except under a separate written
    agreement with NQP LLC
  - Sublicense or relicense NQP's reference source code under any
    other terms
  - Remove, alter, or obscure this license text or the copyright
    notice

This Section A governs copyright in NQP's specific reference source
code only. It does not restrict, and is independent of, the right to
make, use, sell, or distribute an independent conforming implementation
of the Enqpy™ cipher: that right is addressed by the Covenant
summarized in Section B. Writing one's own implementation of the cipher
does not require a copyright license under this Section A.

----------------------------------------------------------------
B. PATENT NON-ASSERTION COVENANT
----------------------------------------------------------------

Definitions

"NQP Patents" means U.S. provisional patent applications 64/030,651;
64/030,659; 64/030,684; 64/030,693; 64/030,698; 64/030,706;
international patent application PCT/US26/22552; and any patents
issuing from any of the foregoing, including continuations,
continuations-in-part, divisions, reissues, and foreign counterparts,
to the extent owned or controlled by NQP LLC.

"Conforming Implementation" means an implementation of the Enqpy™
cipher that conforms to the public specification (the Formal
Cryptographic Description and the published test vectors) — that is,
one that reproduces the specified outputs. Conformance for this purpose
is technical (the implementation behaves as specified); it does not
require Foundation certification.

The Covenant

NQP LLC has granted the Open-Infrastructure Patent Non-Assertion
Covenant, under which NQP LLC irrevocably covenants not to assert the
NQP Patents against any person for making, having made, using, offering
to sell, selling, importing, or distributing a Conforming
Implementation, by anyone and for any purpose, including open-source
implementations, inclusion in libraries and distributions,
standards-track adoption, research and education, public-interest
deployment, and commercial deployment.

The Covenant is irrevocable for the covered field of use, runs with the
NQP Patents, and binds NQP's successors and assignees, so that the
patent safety of the open ecosystem survives any transfer of NQP or the
portfolio. The full Covenant, published at https://enqpy.com/covenant
and in this repository, is the controlling patent instrument; this
Section B is a summary and does not limit it.

Defensive suspension

Consistent with the Covenant, the non-assertion commitment is suspended
as to any person (and that person's Affiliates) who initiates or
voluntarily joins patent litigation (including a cross-claim or
counterclaim) alleging that (a) the Enqpy™ cipher or a Conforming
Implementation infringes any patent, or (b) NQP LLC, Enqpy™ Foundation
Inc., the inventor, or any of their respective directors, officers,
employees, agents, or successors infringes any patent through an act
substantially related to the Enqpy™ cipher, a Conforming
Implementation, or the activities of the Foundation. Suspension,
restoration, and the carve-out for purely defensive assertion operate
as set out in §4 of the Covenant, which controls. "Affiliate" has the
meaning given in §1.6 of the Covenant.

What the Covenant does not grant

The Covenant conveys no rights in the Enqpy™ marks (see Section D), no
copyright license to NQP's reference source beyond Section A, and no
right to claim Foundation certification or "Enqpy™-Certified" /
"Enqpy™-Compatible" status (see Sections C and D).

----------------------------------------------------------------
C. COMMERCIAL RELATIONSHIPS (THE EARNED EDGE)
----------------------------------------------------------------

The Enqpy™ cipher is patent-safe to use, implement, and deploy under
the Covenant, with no fee and no license required for that use. The
following commercial relationships remain available from NQP LLC and
the Enqpy™ Foundation for organizations that want them — they fund the
work and provide assurance, but none is a condition of using the
cipher:

  - Enqpy™ Foundation conformance certification — for third-party
    implementations seeking the Enqpy™-Certified mark and listing in
    the public registry.

  - NQP high-performance proprietary implementations — the optimized
    VHDL/FPGA pipeline and related non-public implementation materials,
    licensed separately as NQP trade-secret/copyright works (not the
    public reference, and not reached by the Covenant).

  - NQP commercial services — architecture review, audit, training,
    custom implementation, integration, advisory, support, SLAs, and
    indemnity.

  - Partner Program — Enqpy-Certified Product, Enqpy Inside Trademark,
    Custom Implementation, Premier Technical, and Hardware Integration.

  - Optional signed patent license and indemnity — for organizations
    that prefer an executed, individually negotiated agreement and
    indemnification, notwithstanding the Covenant's protection of their
    use.

See https://enqpy.com/use.html or email RPM@enqpy.com with
[Commercial] in the subject line.

